    <h1 class="brand-serif">Data Tables in Workhub</h1>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-10">
    <p>Workhub's data tables have been difficult to use for some time. Not only were the data retrieval strategies creaking under their own weight, but a recent move to AWS was proving to be extremely expensive as well (for the same reasons!). Throw that in with a mountain of user feedback about the poor paginatory and other lacking features. The need was clear.</p>
    <p class="mt-4"><strong>The Bet</strong><br />A new “virtual scrolling” table would be built with a new frontend design that would prioritize usability, utility, and actionability. Once a core feature set was established, all tables in the app (over 300) would be redesigned with the new design/development paradigm.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-2"><a class="btn btn-outline-dark mb-4" href="../../">Go back</a></div>
</div>

