  <div class="col-lg-8 offset-lg-2 col-md-8 mb-4 mb-md-0" style="position: relative; z-index: 1;">
    <div class="case-study-info">
      <h5 class="mb-2">How bad could it be?</h5>
      <p>The lack of function was subtle in some ways, and completely in your face in others. Basics like not announcing if a column is sortable, hiding how pagination worked, “chainsaw” alignment (when columns alternate between static sizes and fixed), and many different versions of table styling made it difficult for a user to know what to expect across a day of work.</p>
      <p>I believed we could create a consistently designed set of cells paired with an upgrade in core functionality and data retrieval to give users a much more cohesive experience.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

