      <p>You’ve probably gotten a good sense of the type of cell consistency I was aiming for with this new global control. I built the massively useful (and massively complex) table cell Figma control that handles all the styling consistency. The goal was to collect all the modern iterations of our molecule usage and capture them here. This would allow me granular control over the truncating behaviour mentioned above as well as indenting, shadows, and other highly specific stylings in the UI.</p>
      <p>The ultimate goal was to provide a tool that faded into the background while other talented designers plied their craft building useful and actionable tables.</p>
